							"content:textarea:4:56": {
								"icon": "align-justify",
								"name": "Paragraph",
								"type": "textarea",
								"html": "<p>\n\tThe Woodyard Fund began in <strong>1816</strong>, when the Ladies Benevolent Society provided firewood—and later coal—to struggling families. Around the turn of the 20th century, The Salvation Army took on management of the fund. In 1930, The State newspaper began promoting the effort each winter, a tradition that continued until 2020.\n</p>",
